The paper deals with computer-aided diagnosis based on histopathological imaging using machine learning methodologies, specifically deep Convolutional Neural Nets (CNNs). This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of transfer learning approaches and the proposed adaptive CNN architecture also suggest relevance to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories.
